  "text": "Though motivated by the robot soccer domain, this problem formulation is applicable to general vision-based mobile robots. This paper also serves as a case study demonstrating the practical steps in the process of developing an effective real-time vision system for a mobile robot. A primary distinguishing feature of our task is that the relatively low resolution (and noisy) camera image is the primary sensory input, unlike many other mobile robots where the focus is mainly on laser/sonar sensors [CITATION_1] .",
